{"title_page": "Himmata Ram Bhambhu", "text_new": "[[File:Himmata Ram Bhambhu.jpg|thumb|Himmata Ram Bhambhu]]\n'''Himmata Ram Bhambhu''' is a social worker, [[nature]] lover, [[conservation movement|conservationist]] and [[environmentalist]] from [[Nagaur]] district in [[Rajasthan]], India. He has been awarded with [[Padmashri]], fourth highest civilian award of India,  on Republic-day 26 January 2020 by the [[President of India]].<ref>[https://indiacsr.in/conservationist-himmat-ram-bhambhu-wins-padma-shri/ Conservationist Himmat Ram Bhambhu wins Padma Shri]</ref><ref>https://www.klipinterest.com/conservationist-himmat-ram-bhambhu-wins-padma-shri/ </ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nHe was born on 14.2.1956 at village Sukhwasi in [[Nagaur]] district, [[Rajasthan]], [[India]]. He did his Primary education from school in his own village Sukhwasi in [[Nagaur]] district. He passed 6th standard from middle school Gogelao but could not continue his education due to adverse family conditions.\n\n== Social work ==\nHe has been involved in Planting and preserving trees and motivating people for nature conservation in forest deficit districts like [[Nagaur]], [[Jodhpur]], [[Jaisalmer]], [[Barmer district|Barmer]], [[Sikar]], [[Ajmer]] etc.  since last 30 years. He is associated with Mahavir International Sansthan Nagaur for Green India Mission since 2013.<ref>Mahavir Pravah, September-October 2015,p.19</ref> <ref name=\"Medium2\">[https://medium.com/@gauravit.321203/inspiring-stories-of-our-padma-shri-awardee-of-2020-episode-2-852a77cc675e Inspiring stories of Our Padma Shri Awardee of 2020 \u2014 Episode : 2]</ref>\n\nHe has developed a unique integrated [[agro-forestry]] plantation and [[biodiversity conservation]] centre.  The green patch he has created at village [[Harima]] in [[Nagaur]] in an area of 6 ha has become unique rehabilitation center for Peacocks, Chinkaras and other various rare wild birds and animals. His efforts have been widely appreciated and he has been awarded with many awards. He has been associated with People for Animals programe run by [[Menaka Gandhi]]. <ref name=\"Medium2\" />\n\nHe was invited by the [[President of India]] on 3.1.2020 for discussion on grass-root issues regarding conservation of forest, environment and wild life.   <ref>*[https://www.etvbharat.com/hindi/rajasthan/state/nagore/nagaur-environmental-lover-himmat-ram-bhambhu-meet-president-ramnath-kovind/rj20200108145405382 ETV Rajasthan]</ref>\n\n== Honours and Awards ==\nHe was awarded by UNESCO in 1999 for environment protection. He was an instrument in getting declared Gogelao and Rotoo as conservation reserves. He is an awardee of Rajasthan State Amrita Devi Vishnoi Award for 2003. He was appointed as honorary [[Wildlife|Wild Life]] Warden from 2000-2016 by the Government of Rajasthan. \n\nHe is an awardee of [[Rajiv Gandhi]] Environment Protection Award -2014.\n\nHe is an awardee of Veer [[Durgadas Rathore]] Award-2017.\n\nHe is recipient of Green Warriors Award-2019.\n\nHe was awarded with Sant Ishwar Sewa Award-2019\n\nHe has been awarded with [[Padmashri]] on Republic-day 26 January 2020 by the President of India. <ref>http://www.dashboard-padmaawards.gov.in/?Place=Rajasthan&Award=Padma%20Shri</ref><ref>[https://hindi.news18.com/news/rajasthan/jaipur-himmataram-bhanbu-from-dadi-s-peepal-to-the-highest-honor-padmashri-rjsr-2804761.html hindi.news18.com 26 January 2020]</ref>\n\n== External links ==\n*https://www.patrika.com/nagaur-news/padamshri-awardee-himmataram-bhambhu-himmat-ram-bhambhu-rajasthan-5694803/ \n*https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/nagour/news/rajasthan-news-bhabhu-an-environmental-lover-who-has-planted-3-lakh-trees-will-receive-the-padma-shri-100101-6480634.html \n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:Environmentalists]] \n[[Category:People in environment]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Rajasthani people]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Padma Shri in social work]]\n[[Category:People from Rajasthan]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Himmata Ram Bhambhu.jpg|thumb|Himmata Ram Bhambhu]]\n'''Himmata Ram Bhambhu''' is a social worker, [[nature]] lover, [[conservation movement|conservationist]] and [[environmentalist]] from [[Nagaur]] district in [[Rajasthan]], India. He has been awarded with [[Padmashri]], fourth highest civilian award of India,  on Republic-day 26 January 2020 by the [[President of India]].<ref>[https://indiacsr.in/conservationist-himmat-ram-bhambhu-wins-padma-shri/ Conservationist Himmat Ram Bhambhu wins Padma Shri]</ref><ref>https://www.klipinterest.com/conservationist-himmat-ram-bhambhu-wins-padma-shri/ </ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nHe was born on 14.2.1956 at village Sukhwasi in [[Nagaur]] district, [[Rajasthan]], [[India]]. He did his Primary education from school in his own village Sukhwasi in [[Nagaur]] district. He passed 6th standard from middle school Gogelao but could not continue his education due to adverse family conditions.\n\n== Social work ==\nHe has been involved in Planting and preserving trees and motivating people for nature conservation in forest deficit districts like [[Nagaur]], [[Jodhpur]], [[Jaisalmer]], [[Barmer district|Barmer]], [[Sikar]], [[Ajmer]] etc.  since last 30 years. He is associated with Mahavir International Sansthan Nagaur for Green India Mission since 2013.<ref>Mahavir Pravah, September-October 2015,p.19</ref> <ref>[https://medium.com/@gauravit.321203/inspiring-stories-of-our-padma-shri-awardee-of-2020-episode-2-852a77cc675e Inspiring stories of Our Padma Shri Awardee of 2020 \u2014 Episode : 2]</ref>\n\nHe has developed a unique integrated [[agro-forestry]] plantation and [[biodiversity conservation]] centre.  The green patch he has created at village [[Harima]] in [[Nagaur]] in an area of 6 ha has become unique rehabilitation center for Peacocks, Chinkaras and other various rare wild birds and animals. His efforts have been widely appreciated and he has been awarded with many awards. He has been associated with People for Animals programe run by [[Menaka Gandhi]]. <ref>[https://medium.com/@gauravit.321203/inspiring-stories-of-our-padma-shri-awardee-of-2020-episode-2-852a77cc675e Inspiring stories of Our Padma Shri Awardee of 2020 \u2014 Episode : 2]</ref>\n\nHe was invited by the [[President of India]] on 3.1.2020 for discussion on grass-root issues regarding conservation of forest, environment and wild life.   <ref>*[https://www.etvbharat.com/hindi/rajasthan/state/nagore/nagaur-environmental-lover-himmat-ram-bhambhu-meet-president-ramnath-kovind/rj20200108145405382 ETV Rajasthan]</ref>\n\n== Honours and Awards ==\nHe was awarded by UNESCO in 1999 for environment protection. He was an instrument in getting declared Gogelao and Rotoo as conservation reserves. He is an awardee of Rajasthan State Amrita Devi Vishnoi Award for 2003. He was appointed as honorary [[Wild Life]]{{dn|date=April 2020}} Warden from 2000-2016 by the Government of Rajasthan. \n\nHe is an awardee of [[Rajiv Gandhi]] Environment Protection Award -2014.\n\nHe is an awardee of Veer [[Durgadas Rathore]] Award-2017.\n\nHe is recipient of Green Warriors Award-2019.\n\nHe was awarded with Sant Ishwar Sewa Award-2019\n\nHe has been awarded with [[Padmashri]] on Republic-day 26 January 2020 by the President of India. <ref>http://www.dashboard-padmaawards.gov.in/?Place=Rajasthan&Award=Padma%20Shri</ref><ref>[https://hindi.news18.com/news/rajasthan/jaipur-himmataram-bhanbu-from-dadi-s-peepal-to-the-highest-honor-padmashri-rjsr-2804761.html hindi.news18.com 26 January 2020]</ref>\n\n== External links ==\n*https://www.patrika.com/nagaur-news/padamshri-awardee-himmataram-bhambhu-himmat-ram-bhambhu-rajasthan-5694803/ \n*https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/nagour/news/rajasthan-news-bhabhu-an-environmental-lover-who-has-planted-3-lakh-trees-will-receive-the-padma-shri-100101-6480634.html \n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:Environmentalists]] \n[[Category:People in environment]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Rajasthani people]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Padma Shri in social work]]\n[[Category:People from Rajasthan]]\n", "name_user": "GoingBatty", "label": "safe", "comment": "v2.02 - Repaired 1 link to disambiguation page -(You can help)-Wild Life/WP:WCWproject (Reference duplication)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Himmata_Ram_Bhambhu"}
